nodes.bodyText:
What if the class is an interface or abstract class that a value-based class could implement or be derived from, respectively?

That's a very good question. I experimented with the two cases. isMonitorValueBased() could return either TR_maybe or TR_no.

TR_maybe: because  the object class is not in _monitorMapping.
TR_no because it reaches the end of the isMonitorValueBased() and VM J9_IS_J9CLASS_VALUEBASED returns false; not because if (clazz == self()->comp()->getObjectClassPointer()) is true.

If the base class is an interface or abstract class, it won't hit the path that if (clazz == self()->comp()->getObjectClassPointer()) is true.
pseudo code:
interface A 

@ValueBased
public class B implements A 

Object obj = new B(); 
synchronized(obj) { ... }

A obj = new B(); 
synchronized(obj) { ... }

abstract class C

@ValueBased
public class D extends C {

Object obj = new D(); 
synchronized(obj) { ... }

C obj = new D(); 
synchronized(obj) { ... }

